parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Excessive oil consumption can lead to premature wear on engine components, increased emissions, and potentially cause engine failure, which can result in accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle consumes excessive amounts of oil
the vehicle may emit a burning odor
and the engine may shake or vibrate.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag system can prevent the airbags from deploying in the event of an accident, which can increase the risk of injury or fatality.
symptoms: the airbag system check light is on
the airbag SRS light is on
the airbag warning light illuminates intermittently
the airbag warning light illuminates when pressing the horn pad.
